A Kansas mother who uses marijuana to treat a debilitating disease has lost custody of her 11-year-old son at least temporarily and could face possible charges following comments the boy made during an anti-drug education program at school .
The case of Shona Banda , 37 , was forwarded on Monday to the Finney County district attorney 's office .
Possible charges include possession of marijuana with intent to distribute , possession of drug paraphernalia and child endangerment .
Banda is the author of a book ` Live Free or Die : Reclaim your Country .